I like this place. It's much more sanitary then it's competition on Seaview Ave. Don't ask how I know this.  If your comfort food is Chinese with local interests infused style. This is a good place. Here you will find not so Chinese options as fried apple sticks or fried plantains or French fries. I like the urban American twist.  My recommendation is the: Chicken and Broccoli w/ white rice (Yes, another non Chinese dish). Just a lil warning the rice is undersized for the amount of chicken/broccoli. You may need to order additional rice.  They office delivery or take out. No longer has an eat in option due to COVID-19 issues.  They accept cash only. So, have in mind when you order with them.

Let me start off by saying I’ve been ordering from here for years ! And today they had bad customer service which I do not take lightly. I called them about 6:21pm and I parked my car right in front and walked in around 6:23pm and I handed the money to her and she put it away and came back with my food about 2 minutes after. I’m not thinking about the timing until I see the fries looked hard and slightly burnt and the chicken was dark & fried hard as well. I said “the fries look hard” and then she ignored it and ask what sauce I wanted and I replied ketchup and bbq sauce. Then I’m thinking that was cooked fast ! So I went on to ask can I taste the fries and I taste two which were hard ! I asked her nicely may you make the batch of fries over because it’s to hard and she said no we can’t and the guy standing with her said this is how we always cooked them. I said sir the fries are hard and the chicken is dark (anytime I order the fries are not hard and the chicken is not hard either and mind you I’m just coming from work so I’m tired) and I always come here you can’t change the fries ? He said no and you can take your money back with an attitude. And I gladly took my money back and they kept the food. He was also hesitant in giving me the money back as if he wanted me to settle and change my mind. Nope 👎 not going here anymore and will not recommend them to anyone. Make sure you check your food if it comes out fast I learned my lesson. Lost a customer.
